{
  "stem": "3952.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The water was very good, but you have to go out and bring it in from the well.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had two cows to maintain us with milk.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my sisters and my mother they would make butter, and they would make cheese out of that milk.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So only the-- the minimal-- the minimum was there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother used to bake bread twice a week.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "On Tuesday morning, she would get up at 3 o'clock in the morning, make the dough, bake the bread.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When the-- when the daughters were bigger they were-- they would help, especially one of them who lives in Israel now, because she wasn't working out of the house.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The others were working out of the house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that bread, the taste and the smell of that bread is something that you guys in America, who were born in America, will never know and never feel.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That that very good.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was very good.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So you can say that Tuesday morning and Friday morning when she would make those pitas, special pitas for breakfast, that was a happy moment for me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But those were the kind of moments that we-- that we had, happy moments that I have in recollection that I can recollect as a child, from my childhood.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we knew about anti-semitism because they kicked my father out the minute the Hungarians took over.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The next day, he was out of his position.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But experiencing it per se-- the first instant that I remember anti-semitism was I had a-- a non-Jewish friend who every day came to my house after school that I make his homework for him.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was the first one to throw me off the sidewalk and say, [SPEAKING HUNGARIAN].",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
